  + Validation: API key required for cloud providers, endpoint required for
    all providers.
  + [FIXED] Test API button added — users can verify configuration before
    starting sorting.
  + [FIXED] Model recommendation label added — guides users on model
    selection.
  + [FIXED] Disclaimer note added about token prices — acknowledges prices
    may change.
  + [FIXED] Budget cap spinner added — users can set a maximum spend limit.


==============================================================================
SCREEN 7: REVIEW SCREEN (show_review_summary)
==============================================================================

UI Design Grade:  B
Feature Grade:    B+

LAYOUT & VISUAL HIERARCHY
  + Summary stats at the top as colored boxes (Keep=green, Delete=red,
    Skip=orange, Move=blue, Copy=purple) with large count numbers (24px
    bold) — immediately communicates the session outcome.
  + Editable table with per-file decision combos and destination dropdowns
    — full control before committing.
  + Bulk action buttons (All Keep, All Skip, All Pending) above the table
    — efficient for mass changes.
  + "Execute All" button is green, bold, with padding — clear primary
    action with appropriate gravity.
  + Virtual folder creation note in orange italic — warns about folders
    that will be created.
  - The table creates a combo box for every file row — with 1000+ files,
    this will be slow and memory-heavy. No virtualization.
  + [FIXED] Filter and sort combos added to the review table — can group
    by decision type or destination folder.
  - No visual grouping by destination folder — files assigned to the same
    folder are scattered throughout the table sorted by their original
    scan order.
  - Destination combo shows folder basenames only — two folders named
    "Images" in different paths would be ambiguous.
  - Mode column exists but is mostly redundant in single-mode sessions —
    only useful when switching between Basic/Advanced/AI mid-session.
  - No drag-and-drop reordering or reassignment.
  + [FIXED] Decision-based color coding added — visual diff of what will
    change.

FEATURES
  + Every decision is editable: decision type (keep/delete/skip/move/copy/
    pending) and destination folder (dropdown or typed path).
  + Bulk actions: All Keep, All Skip, All Pending — efficient for common
    operations.
  + Destination combo includes all grid folders, with "[virtual]" tags for
    folders that don't exist yet.
  + Typed paths support relative paths (auto-prefixed with source folder).
  + Virtual folder creation with failure handling — if a folder can't be
    created, files targeting it are skipped with user confirmation.
  + Copy execution (QFile::copy) runs before the executor for move/delete.
  + [FIXED] Hover preview toggle added for files in the review table.
  - No size information in the table — can't identify large files.
  - No "undo all" or "revert to pending" for a subset of files.
  + [FIXED] Keyboard shortcut hints added for navigation within the review
    table.
  + [FIXED] The cancel button styled gray — visual distinction from primary
    action.


==============================================================================
SCREEN 8: EXECUTION RESULTS SCREEN (show_execution_results)
==============================================================================

UI Design Grade:  B+
Feature Grade:    A-

LAYOUT & VISUAL HIERARCHY
  + Session Statistics groupbox with formatted text showing total files,
    per-category counts, execution time, and operation counts — comprehensive
    summary.
  + Review pace metric ("~X files/minute") in blue italic — gamification
    element that encourages efficiency.
  + Error messages in red — immediately visible.
  + Execution log table with per-action Undo buttons — inline action.
  + Undo buttons are orange with "Undo" text; disabled permanently deleted
    files show "Permanent" with tooltip explanation — clear affordance.
  + Close button is green and bold — clear exit action.
  + [FIXED] Filter combo added to the execution log table — can filter
    by action type for large sessions.
  - Successful undos change button text to "Done" and action text to
    "(undone)" but the row stays in place — could be confusing as the
    table fills with completed undos.
  + [FIXED] Disk space freed summary shown (e.g., "freed X MB of disk
    space").

FEATURES
  + Per-action undo: each move/delete can be individually reversed —
    granular control.
  + Undo updates the database (removes from execution log) — persistent.
  + Permanent deletion detection: files deleted without trash path have
    disabled undo with "Permanent" label and tooltip.
  + Execution time tracking — useful for comparing sorting efficiency
    across sessions.
  + Error count with detailed error messages.
  + [FIXED] Undo All button added for batch undo.
  + [FIXED] Export Log to CSV added for the execution log.
  + [FIXED] Disk space impact summary shown in stats.
  - Session statistics count reviewed files (decisions made) but the stats
    show the counts from BEFORE execution — if execution partially failed,
    the displayed counts don't reflect actual outcomes.


==============================================================================
SCREEN 9: FILE LIST WINDOW (FileListWindow)
==============================================================================

UI Design Grade:  B+
Feature Grade:    B+

LAYOUT & VISUAL HIERARCHY
  + Compact tool window (Qt::Tool | Qt::WindowStaysOnTopHint) — stays
    visible alongside the main sorting screen without modal blocking.
  + Filter bar at top — immediately accessible.
  + File list with decision status prefixes ([K], [D], [S], [M], [C], [ ])
    — decision state visible without clicking.
  + Color-coded decisions: green=keep, red=delete, gray=skip, blue=move,
    purple=copy — consistent with the rest of the app.
  + Current file highlighted with bold font and darker background — clear
    positional indicator.
  + Status bar showing "X / Y files" and "Z selected" — context awareness.
  + Usage tip at the bottom in small gray text — guides new users.
  + [FIXED] Palette-adaptive styling — respects the global theme setting
    instead of hardcoded dark theme colors.
  + [FIXED] Sort combo added — files can be sorted beyond scan order.
  + [FIXED] Minimum size reduced to 280x320 — appropriate for a secondary
    tool window.

FEATURES
  + Filter-as-you-type with QLineEdit — fast file search.
  + Multi-selection via ExtendedSelection — Shift/Ctrl click.
  + Right-click context menu for batch assignment to folders — efficient
    for assigning multiple files to the same destination.
  + Single-click navigates to file in main window (with modifier key
    detection — doesn't navigate during multi-select).
  + Double-click also navigates.
  + Refresh method updates the list when the main window's state changes.
  + Destination folders provided via set_destination_folders().
  - No drag-and-drop FROM the list TO folder buttons — must use context
    menu.
  - No way to change decisions from the list (only assignment via
    right-click).
  - File list reconstructs entirely on every update (clear + rebuild) —
    could be expensive for large file sets.
  - Each right-click context menu shows ALL destination folders — no
    search/filter for the destination.
  + [FIXED] File size shown in list items — names, status, and size info.


==============================================================================
SCREEN 10: IMAGE PREVIEW WINDOW (ImagePreviewWindow)
==============================================================================

UI Design Grade:  A-
Feature Grade:    A-

LAYOUT & VISUAL HIERARCHY
  + Full-featured preview window with toolbar: Prev/Next navigation, zoom
    controls (-, slider, +, percentage label), Fit/1:1 buttons, file info.
  + 80% of screen size by default — large enough for meaningful preview.
  + Scroll area with center alignment and dark background (#1a1a1a) —
    image content stands out.
  + Zoom slider (10%-500%) — precise control with visual feedback.
  + File info label shows "filename | WxH | size" — essential metadata.
