  + [FIXED] Column sorting enabled — can sort by size or date within groups.
  + [FIXED] Delete button count change styled bold + brighter — transition
    from "Delete Selected" to "Delete Selected (3)" is more noticeable.

FEATURES
  + Two-phase detection: Phase 1 uses name+size matching (fast), Phase 2
    adds SHA-256 hash verification (content-level accuracy).
  + Multi-selection with ExtendedSelection — select multiple files across
    groups.
  + Confirmation dialog before marking for deletion.
  + Marked files visually tagged: red text + "[marked for delete]" suffix +
    disabled state — clear post-action feedback.
  + Files are marked for deletion (not immediately deleted) — integrates
    with the review/execute flow.
  + Tooltips showing full file paths.
  - Hash verification reads files in 64KB chunks — good, but no progress
    indicator during hashing. Large files could cause a freeze (uses
    QApplication::processEvents but only batch-level, not per-file).
  + [FIXED] Keep Newest button added — option to keep newest and delete
    rest.
  - No file preview from the duplicate window — must navigate back to main.
  - No size savings preview ("deleting these would free X MB").
  + [FIXED] SHA-256 used for hashing — replaced deprecated MD5. For
    duplicate detection this is more robust and avoids user concerns.


