==============================================================================
CROSS-CUTTING OBSERVATIONS
==============================================================================

THEME CONSISTENCY
  +/- [PARTIALLY FIXED] Theme-aware tooltips added — dark theme colors
    still hardcoded in many screens (#2c3e50, #34495e, #1e1e1e, #2d2d2d,
    etc.) but tooltip styling now respects the palette. The light theme
    toggle changes QPalette but many widgets still ignore the palette
    due to inline stylesheet overrides.
  - No high-contrast mode or accessibility support across any screen.

INTERACTION PATTERNS
  + Consistent keyboard shortcuts across modes (Left=Delete, Down=Skip,
    Z=Undo) — muscle memory transfers.
  + Consistent color coding across all screens (green=keep, red=delete,
    orange=skip, blue=move, purple=copy).
  + Context menus available on right-click throughout — power user friendly.
  + [FIXED] Tooltips added for middle-click interactions (remove from Quick
    Access, remove from recent folders) and double-click-to-open-file —
    these interactions are now discoverable.

INFORMATION ARCHITECTURE
  + Three-mode progression (Basic → Advanced → AI) is well-conceived: each
    mode genuinely builds on the previous without duplicating UI.
  + Session state preservation across mode switches — seamless transitions.
  + Review → Execute → Results flow is consistent across all modes.
  - No unified settings/preferences screen — settings are scattered across
    QSettings (theme), SQLite (sessions, AI providers), and hardcoded values
    (UI dimensions).
  - No help system beyond keyboard shortcut labels — no tutorial, no
    guided walkthrough, no documentation accessible from within the app.

PERFORMANCE CONSIDERATIONS
  + QImageReader::setScaledSize() for preview loading — avoids full decode.
  + Progress dialogs for operations >200 files — UI stays responsive.
  + Debounced resize events — prevents stutter.
  +/- [PARTIALLY FIXED] Performance note added for large data sets — review
    screen creates N combo boxes upfront (O(n) widget creation).
  - FileListWindow rebuilds entirely on every update.
  - MindMapView rebuilds entire grid on every model change.
  - No full virtualization — large data sets may still cause slowdowns.


